The paper discusses the development of a new approach for graph data management and analysis based on the Hadoop ecosystem, which is a distributed computing framework commonly used in big data applications. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DB (databases) sub-category, which deals with the storage, retrieval, and management of large amounts of data. Additionally, the paper focuses on graph data, which is a type of structured data commonly used in social network analysis and other applications, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of high-level operators and a domain-specific language for analyzing graph data, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (social and information networks) or cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-categories, which deal with the analysis and processing of large-scale data sets. Finally, the paper discusses the use of Gradoop for business intelligence, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SY (systems and control) sub-category, which deals with the design and implementation of large-scale systems.
